<br>
There are few classes pvpwise that can match a well played bard (though good pvp bards are few and far between). Their healing, evasion/pursuit, resists, ability to quickly annul (themselves and you) and the ability to poof pets means that mages should always avoid these confrontations where possible.<br>
<br>
Below level 46, mages stand a pretty good chance against a bard though as the bards won't have their two main DOT songs to stack on you. Their melee output at these levels (under most conditions) is minor.<br>
<br>
But the general rule is: even a mostly incompetant bard would eat a skilled mage alive. <p><table width=100%><tr><td width=50%><font color=blue><i><b>Svenuce Summonstuff</b></i></font><br>
